    "description": "We at Boehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services are looking for an experienced Surgeon based out of Agra. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Boehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services:\nBoehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Learning & development budget\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Boehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services!",
